---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CtaBand from '@components/CtaBand.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About | Cumberland Septic Hub"
  description="What Cumberland Septic Hub is, what it does and does not do, and how it helps Upper Cumberland property owners request septic service from independent local providers."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]} />
      <h1>About Cumberland Septic Hub</h1>
      <p>A regional septic resource for the Upper Cumberland — built to make requesting service simpler and better informed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="container prose" style="max-width:52rem;">
      <h2>What this website is</h2>
      <p>
        Cumberland Septic Hub is an independent referral and information resource focused on one
        region — Cookeville, Crossville and the wider Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee — and one
        subject: septic systems. It exists to do two things well. First, help property owners
        understand what their symptoms might mean, what different services involve, and what
        information makes a service request useful. Second, connect those requests with
        independent local septic providers who actually do the work.
      </p>

      <h2>What this website is not</h2>
      <p>
        Cumberland Septic Hub is not a septic contractor. It does not employ technicians, own
        trucks, hold contractor licenses or maintain a physical service office, and it does not
        perform septic pumping, repair, inspection or installation unless expressly stated.
        Provider availability, qualifications, licensing, insurance, pricing, scheduling,
        warranties and service terms are determined independently by each provider.
      </p>

      <h2>Why the region focus matters</h2>
      <p>
        Septic service is local by nature — trucks, soils, county practices and provider ranges
        all vary. A regional resource can describe the Upper Cumberland’s actual conditions:
        plateau properties around <a href="/septic-pumping-crossville-tn/">Crossville</a>, lake
        country near <a href="/septic-services-smithville-tn/">Smithville</a> and
        <a href="/septic-services-livingston-tn/">Livingston</a>, farmland around
        <a href="/septic-services-sparta-tn/">Sparta</a>, and the growing edges of
        <a href="/septic-pumping-cookeville-tn/">Cookeville</a> itself.
      </p>

      <h2>How to use it</h2>
      <p>
        Read the service pages to understand what you are dealing with, then use the
        <a href="/request-service/">request form</a> to describe the property and the problem.
        The <a href="/how-referrals-work/">how referrals work</a> page explains what happens
        after you submit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CtaBand />
</Base>
